  "text": "The molluscicide niclosamide dissolved in dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO) was purchased from Sigma. Uninfected and S. mansoni-infected B. pfeifferi were exposed to a concentration of 0.15 mg/L niclosamide with final DMSO concentrations at 1/1000 (v/v) for 24 hours at 26-28C with aeration [CITATION_1] . Previous 24 h exposure of B. glabrata to varying doses of niclosamide (0.05mg/L, 0.10mg/L, and 0.15mg/L) found that the 0.15mg/L dose produced the most robust transcriptional response, as assessed by microarray analysis [CITATION_2] .",
